ming to hit the reduced target.\nPlan for next week: Reduce scope to the top-2 use cases and land a partial fix.\n\nBLOCKERS / RISKS\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [March]: Rate-limiter fairness audit: Owner is oncall this week; capacity is halved.\n  Leader Engineer: Ines Ashby | Owner: Ines Ashby | Days open: n/a\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [March]: Observability sampling refresh: Downstream integration test suite is flaky; may hide a regression at go-live.\n  Leader Engineer: Bea Sardar | Owner: Bea Sardar | Days open: n/a\n- [Risk] Q1 2026 [March]: Config drift auto-repair: Reviewer coverage is thin the week of launch — flagging in case rollout slips.\n  Leader Engineer: Bea Sardar | Owner: Bea Sardar | Days open: n/a\n\nKind Regards\nEngineering Manager"
